WEBVTT

00:04.320 --> 00:06.560
TOMMY: <i>Oh, there's a woman.</i>

00:08.360 --> 00:09.360
Yeah.

00:10.800 --> 00:11.800
A woman.

00:14.000 --> 00:15.400
Who I love.

00:17.560 --> 00:19.000
And I got close.

00:30.520 --> 00:32.320
In the bleak midwinter...

00:37.400 --> 00:39.360
At some point in the near future,

00:39.440 --> 00:41.760
Mr Churchill will want to speak to you
in person.

00:42.560 --> 00:43.680
Mr Shelby,

00:45.040 --> 00:46.560
he has a job for you.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.120
(PANTING)

00:48.200 --> 00:49.440
We will be in touch.

01:09.960 --> 01:11.960
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:12.520 --> 01:13.520
(CHURCH BELLS CHIMING)

01:20.640 --> 01:22.520
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:24.200 --> 01:25.840
Oh, thank you.

01:38.840 --> 01:40.360
-(BABY CRYING)
-I'm going to take him.

01:48.800 --> 01:50.280
Some of us know the words.

02:19.480 --> 02:20.840
Trot on.

02:23.560 --> 02:27.920
(SINGING) <i># In the bleak mid.winter</i>

02:28.000 --> 02:32.520
<i># Frosty wind made moan</i>

02:32.600 --> 02:36.480
<i># Earth stood hard as iron</i>

02:36.560 --> 02:37.880
Trot on.

02:37.960 --> 02:39.600
<i># Water like a stone</i>

02:39.680 --> 02:40.680
Trot on.

02:42.640 --> 02:47.520
<i># Snow had fallen, snow on snow</i>

02:47.600 --> 02:51.440
<i># Snow on snow</i>

02:52.680 --> 02:57.360
<i># In the bleak mid.winter</i>

02:57.440 --> 03:01.640
<i># Long ago #</i>

03:11.120 --> 03:12.880
(ORGAN PLAYS <i>BRIDAL CHORUS)</i>

03:16.960 --> 03:20.000
Here come the fucking cavalry.
Late as usual.

04:06.240 --> 04:08.000
JEREMIAH: Dearly beloved.

04:08.080 --> 04:12.440
We are gathered here today
to join together in holy matrimony

04:12.960 --> 04:16.840
Thomas Michael Shelby
and Grace Helen Burgess.

04:29.120 --> 04:30.120
(INDISTINCT)

04:35.400 --> 04:37.040
MAID: Those flowers need to go there.

04:42.120 --> 04:44.040
JEREMIAH:
<i>Do you, Thomas Michael Shelby,</i>

04:44.760 --> 04:47.880
take Grace Helen Burgess
to be your lawful wedded wife?

04:49.480 --> 04:50.560
TOMMY: <i>I do.</i>

04:52.320 --> 04:54.520
Do you, Grace Helen Burgess,

04:54.600 --> 04:58.000
solemnly swear to love, hon our,

04:58.080 --> 05:01.520
<i>and obey till death do you part?</i>

05:01.600 --> 05:02.640
GRACE: <i>I do.</i>

05:02.720 --> 05:05.960
JEREMIAH: <i>I now pronounce you
husband and wife.</i>

05:13.400 --> 05:15.280
(ALL CHEERING)

05:33.840 --> 05:35.040
Get out of it!

05:35.120 --> 05:36.800
(ALL TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

05:44.000 --> 05:46.520
-Go on, take the photograph!
-(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

06:01.280 --> 06:03.320
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

06:09.160 --> 06:10.160
Tommy.

06:12.320 --> 06:15.480
Arthur, get the bastards in the house.

06:15.560 --> 06:20.280
I will. I will. John! John-Boy!
Get 'em in the house, all of 'em.

06:23.040 --> 06:25.080
Go on, all of you! Back to the house!
Go on!

06:25.720 --> 06:27.440
(ALL CHEERING)

06:52.320 --> 06:54.240
(ALL CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

07:04.720 --> 07:06.760
(ORCHESTRA PLAYING)

07:30.920 --> 07:34.240
All right, Pol. Tell the Lee girls
I've counted all the paintings.

07:34.320 --> 07:37.200
And, Pol, some people here
are not on the list.

07:39.640 --> 07:41.640
Curly, Charlie. Kitchen.

07:41.720 --> 07:43.680
-Time?
-Five minutes.

07:43.760 --> 07:46.720
Actually, we were told on the train
there'd be cocaine.

07:47.800 --> 07:50.360
Jeremiah, John-Boy, kitchen, let's go.

07:50.440 --> 07:53.160
I swear to God them fucking Cavalry boys
are asking for it.

07:53.240 --> 07:56.440
Uh, I was told to ask someone young.
Will there be cocaine?

07:56.520 --> 07:59.960
Sweetheart, I am young, informed
and, uh, very well-equipped.

08:00.040 --> 08:01.480
You chose your man wisely.

08:02.520 --> 08:04.320
Come on, kitchen now.

08:04.400 --> 08:06.280
Arthur, this lady
wants to play in the snow.

08:06.360 --> 08:08.880
No, no snow today. No snow today.

08:11.080 --> 08:12.720
ARTHUR: <i>Kitchen, come on.</i>

08:12.800 --> 08:14.560
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

08:16.520 --> 08:18.240
(ALL LAUGHING)

08:21.000 --> 08:23.160
I just wish Tommy was here.

08:39.880 --> 08:41.400
-Where are they?
-JOHNNY: I don't know, Tommy.

08:41.480 --> 08:42.800
-Arthur, John, where are they?
-I don't know.

08:42.880 --> 08:45.680
-I am telling you now, we got lost.
-Come on.

08:45.760 --> 08:48.520
You really need to do a map.

08:56.560 --> 08:59.040
Right, boys, you're all here.

09:01.760 --> 09:04.680
Today, this is my fucking wedding day.

09:04.760 --> 09:07.200
Yeah, and you said
there'd be no bloody uniforms.

09:07.280 --> 09:09.880
Nevertheless... Nevertheless, John...

09:09.960 --> 09:12.240
Despite the bad blood,

09:12.320 --> 09:14.120
I'll have none of it on my carpet.

09:14.200 --> 09:17.200
Now for Grace's sake,
nothing will go wrong.

09:17.280 --> 09:20.920
Those bastards out there are her family.

09:21.000 --> 09:25.400
And if you fuckers do anything
to embarrass her,

09:25.480 --> 09:30.960
your kin, your cousins, your horses,
your fucking kids, you do anything...

09:31.040 --> 09:32.720
-JOHN: Tom?
-To... What?

09:32.800 --> 09:33.800
What about snow?

09:34.360 --> 09:36.560
Yeah, their women are sports,
I'll say that...

09:36.640 --> 09:38.560
No. No. No.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.040
No cocaine.

09:42.280 --> 09:44.320
No cocaine. No sport.

09:44.400 --> 09:46.760
No telling fortunes. No racing.

09:46.840 --> 09:50.720
No fucking sucking petrol
out of their fucking cars.

09:52.320 --> 09:55.640
And, you, Charlie,
stop spinning yarns about me, eh?

09:55.720 --> 09:57.760
I'm just trying to sell you
to them, Tom.

09:59.400 --> 10:00.560
But the main thing is,

10:01.400 --> 10:02.760
you bunch of fuckers,

10:03.320 --> 10:06.160
despite the provocation
from the cavalry,

10:06.880 --> 10:08.080
no fighting.

10:09.280 --> 10:10.280
Oi!

10:11.880 --> 10:13.080
No fighting.

10:13.160 --> 10:14.280
No fucking fighting.

10:14.960 --> 10:15.960
No fighting.

10:16.920 --> 10:20.440
(SHOUTING) No fucking fighting!

10:22.200 --> 10:23.200
Good.

10:23.640 --> 10:25.880
-Get the fuck off me!
-(GLASS SHATTERS)

10:32.960 --> 10:34.280
You're needed downstairs.

10:34.520 --> 10:35.800
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:38.440 --> 10:40.120
Grace, you're needed downstairs.

10:40.200 --> 10:41.400
People are hungry.

10:42.240 --> 10:44.240
I was putting Charles to sleep. (SIGHS)

10:44.840 --> 10:46.840
I'll come down,
but not with you like this.

10:46.920 --> 10:48.040
All right, fine.

10:49.120 --> 10:50.280
GRACE: Tommy.

10:51.920 --> 10:56.080
I thought today was the reason
for the way you've been acting lately.

10:56.160 --> 10:58.440
I know there's business on your mind.

11:00.040 --> 11:02.080
-And I know there always will be.
-Yeah.

11:02.160 --> 11:04.640
Look, I am sorry
that they wore their uniforms.

11:04.720 --> 11:07.560
Yeah, they fucking did, eh.
They fucking did.

11:07.640 --> 11:09.320
But I can tell it's more than that.

11:11.680 --> 11:13.640
You've been like this for weeks.

11:15.880 --> 11:17.200
(CLEARS THROAT)

11:18.320 --> 11:20.560
I need you to tell me

11:21.320 --> 11:23.320
that it's business making you like this.

11:23.400 --> 11:25.320
And not regret over me.

11:26.560 --> 11:28.160
Say it out loud
and I'll know if it's true.

11:29.520 --> 11:30.840
(CLICKS TONGUE)

11:33.120 --> 11:34.560
It's business, Grace.

11:37.320 --> 11:39.440
And bad, bad business it is, all around.

11:45.120 --> 11:47.120
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

11:47.200 --> 11:48.840
And I'm scared, Grace.

11:50.240 --> 11:51.760
I'm scared for you.

11:51.840 --> 11:53.400
I'm scared for the baby.

11:53.840 --> 11:55.040
And this is how I am when I'm scared.

11:55.120 --> 11:57.240
It is unfamiliar to you, but not to me.

11:57.320 --> 12:02.160
I can... I can fucking be scared
and carry on.

12:06.240 --> 12:09.120
And it's not pleasant to look at
and no joy to be around.

12:10.800 --> 12:12.160
All right?

12:15.240 --> 12:17.400
I'm sorry. (SNIFFS)

12:24.360 --> 12:26.440
We just made vows to share everything.

12:28.840 --> 12:31.000
Tell me what it is you're afraid of.

12:41.080 --> 12:43.200
-(MUSIC PLAYING)
-(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

12:55.000 --> 12:57.200
Stand up. Stand up, stand up.

12:59.920 --> 13:01.080
Arthur's speech.

13:02.640 --> 13:04.320
I'm scared of fucking Arthur's speech.

13:07.800 --> 13:08.920
All right?

13:10.240 --> 13:11.560
Me, too.

13:15.240 --> 13:16.960
Tommy, what are you doing?

13:17.040 --> 13:18.080
Tommy.

13:18.160 --> 13:22.040
There's half the British Army
waiting for us downstairs.

13:22.560 --> 13:26.920
They're King's Irish.
We waited two weeks in the mud for them.

13:28.360 --> 13:30.480
Tommy. (GIGGLES)

13:32.240 --> 13:36.240
There are things, that if I take them
off, I won't be able to put back on...

13:36.320 --> 13:38.280
-That's good.
-(CHUCKLES)

13:45.600 --> 13:47.160
Hello, Mrs Shelby.

13:48.280 --> 13:51.200
-I'm sorry for being busy in my head.
-(CHUCKLES)

13:53.360 --> 13:55.200
Now let's complete the ceremony.

13:57.280 --> 13:59.160
Hey, listen. Listen, listen.

13:59.240 --> 14:02.560
What do you call an animal
with a prick halfway up its back?

14:03.280 --> 14:05.480
A cavalry horse. (LAUGHING)

14:06.240 --> 14:07.720
He got... He gets it.

14:10.440 --> 14:12.280
Fuck it. Fuck it.

14:12.360 --> 14:14.520
Where the bloody hell are they?
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

14:14.600 --> 14:17.400
You're best man, Arthur.
Go and find them.

14:19.320 --> 14:20.480
Yeah.

14:21.800 --> 14:23.280
ADA: That's completely nonsense.

14:23.360 --> 14:26.400
You know, we're part of a serious
political movement and organisation.

14:26.480 --> 14:29.800
They're not "secret little meetings,"
they're just meetings.

14:29.880 --> 14:32.000
We talk about the world,
about the people in it,

14:32.080 --> 14:34.960
about our current political landscape
and what's going on.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.080
You know, we really need to re-evaluate
the way our government...

14:37.160 --> 14:38.720
(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

14:41.040 --> 14:43.480
-POLLY: He's strange.
-He's looking over.

14:43.560 --> 14:44.560
What?

14:46.880 --> 14:48.840
He's coming. He bloody is.

14:50.880 --> 14:52.920
Fuck. It's the wrong one.

14:53.600 --> 14:55.280
What do you mean "the wrong one"?
How many are there?

14:55.360 --> 14:56.960
There's two, giving me the eye.

14:57.040 --> 14:59.000
I prefer the other one.
He looks harmless.

15:01.680 --> 15:04.600
It must be that bloody lipstick
Tommy brought you back from New York.

15:09.120 --> 15:11.680
I couldn't help noticing
you are unaccompanied.

15:11.760 --> 15:15.320
I also am alone. May I join you?

15:23.680 --> 15:26.200
ARTHUR: Tommy?
Oh. (SNIFFLES)

15:26.880 --> 15:30.640
Didn't see a thing. Did not see a thing.
Sorry, brother.

15:31.680 --> 15:33.120
I need you downstairs.

15:33.720 --> 15:35.200
It's all right. We're done. (SIGHS)

15:35.280 --> 15:36.480
-You good?
-Yeah.

15:36.560 --> 15:37.920
-Never been better.
-Yeah?

15:38.000 --> 15:39.600
-Are you drunk?
-Huh? No.

15:40.400 --> 15:41.400
No.

15:43.360 --> 15:44.360
Here.

15:47.720 --> 15:49.760
All right, it's just one drink, then.

15:50.280 --> 15:52.080
Linda's a good woman, Arthur.

15:56.720 --> 15:57.880
Good whisky.

15:59.400 --> 16:01.680
A good man needs to
hold out sometimes, eh?

16:07.000 --> 16:08.320
(SIGHS)

16:08.760 --> 16:13.200
So, uh, do I mention this
in my speech, then, eh?

16:13.280 --> 16:15.800
Not unless you want to get cut, Arthur.

16:15.880 --> 16:17.200
ARTHUR: Sorry, sister.

16:18.400 --> 16:19.800
TOMMY: Right. Look.

16:20.520 --> 16:22.480
Tell the maids
to break out the champagne.

16:22.560 --> 16:23.920
We'll be down in a minute.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
Champagne, yeah. OK.

16:26.840 --> 16:29.200
-I got it right here. I'm ready.
-Good. Good.

16:33.520 --> 16:35.080
Where are you from?

16:40.680 --> 16:41.720
I'm a refugee.

16:43.440 --> 16:44.440
From where?

16:50.000 --> 16:51.240
Russia.

16:53.480 --> 16:54.560
In the past few months,

16:54.640 --> 16:57.440
Thomas has developed
some business interests with Russia.

16:59.480 --> 17:01.520
I see he has confided in you.

17:03.920 --> 17:04.960
Hmm.

17:05.040 --> 17:07.560
You need his permission
to even speak to me.

17:11.200 --> 17:13.840
My senior position
within the Shelby company

17:13.920 --> 17:17.560
means I don't often have
to ask permission from anyone

17:17.640 --> 17:19.040
to do anything.

17:19.720 --> 17:21.480
So perhaps you'll just tell me

17:21.560 --> 17:26.000
why the fuck you're talking Russian
business on Thomas's wedding day.

17:27.720 --> 17:30.120
LIZZIE: Hold on, wait a second. So
you're saying I'm not allowed a man...

17:30.200 --> 17:31.520
It's about your choice of man.

17:31.600 --> 17:32.760
LIZZIE: I'm not allowed a man on my arm?

17:32.840 --> 17:34.280
MICHAEL: Thomas says
that they're the rules.

17:34.360 --> 17:36.280
LIZZIE: Fucking parish bastard!

17:36.360 --> 17:38.760
Michael, speeches. Come on.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.680
Arthur. You know
why he didn't come, don't you?

17:41.760 --> 17:43.120
Why who didn't come?

17:43.200 --> 17:44.600
My bloody man.

17:44.680 --> 17:46.200
Oh, you mean the wop?

17:46.280 --> 17:50.480
LIZZIE: I just heard there was a fire
at his restaurant midnight last night.

17:50.560 --> 17:53.000
And a smashed back window
and a smell of petrol.

17:53.640 --> 17:56.200
Lizzie, we tried to talk some sense
into you.

17:56.720 --> 17:58.000
We did checks on him.

17:58.080 --> 18:00.000
He's had five different names
in the last six years,

18:00.080 --> 18:01.720
and he's got connections
with the Naples boys.

18:01.800 --> 18:02.800
ARTHUR: Come on, Michael.

18:02.880 --> 18:04.280
What do you know about love?

18:04.360 --> 18:06.160
About when lightning strikes.

18:06.240 --> 18:10.000
So, it was lightning, hmm? Not petrol.

18:11.080 --> 18:12.360
I thought you were
off the whisky, Arthur.

18:12.440 --> 18:14.880
Yeah, I am. Having a couple
now and again

18:14.960 --> 18:16.320
to remind myself why I don't drink it.

18:16.400 --> 18:17.440
(CHUCKLES)

18:17.520 --> 18:20.440
You set fire to his restaurant
to stop him coming.

18:20.520 --> 18:23.720
You have no right to choose
who I step out with in my own time!

18:28.440 --> 18:29.840
(MICHAEL CLEARS THROAT)

18:34.560 --> 18:39.480
Lizzie, you now have an important
position in this company.

18:40.560 --> 18:43.600
You got the order, same as us.

18:45.680 --> 18:47.400
You can do it.

18:52.120 --> 18:54.240
Until further notice...

18:55.280 --> 18:57.680
No fraternizing with the foreigners.

19:01.400 --> 19:02.920
Yeah, well, you can tell Tommy from me

19:03.000 --> 19:05.640
all the girls in the office think
he's losing his fucking mind!

19:11.360 --> 19:12.680
To the bride.

19:12.760 --> 19:13.960
ALL: The bride.

19:14.040 --> 19:15.480
-The bride.
-The bride.

19:18.280 --> 19:22.520
And now, (CLEARS THROAT)
according to tradition,

19:22.600 --> 19:25.000
my best man will say a few words.

19:25.200 --> 19:30.080
Go on! Here he goes! Go on, Arthur!

19:34.400 --> 19:37.600
I'd like to, erm...
I'm not one for speeches.

19:37.680 --> 19:39.920
-Sing, then!
-ARTHUR: I will later, John.

19:41.320 --> 19:43.920
But, er... I do, er...

19:44.920 --> 19:47.680
I do have some words written down here

19:49.560 --> 19:51.200
on this piece of paper.

19:52.520 --> 19:57.400
This doesn't include everything
that I want to say.

19:57.480 --> 19:59.600
Arthur, just, uh...
Just read what we wrote down, eh?

20:00.800 --> 20:03.960
-I will. I will.
-Mmm-hmm.

20:04.040 --> 20:05.280
But...

20:06.320 --> 20:10.640
First... First, uh, a few words from...
From the heart.

20:14.480 --> 20:15.480
Um...

20:17.000 --> 20:19.640
This man here, my brother Tommy,

20:20.800 --> 20:25.000
helped me survive through
some of the worst times.

20:25.120 --> 20:26.720
(COUGHS AND CLEARS THROAT)

20:26.800 --> 20:28.880
It's a wedding, Arthur, tell a joke.

20:28.960 --> 20:30.120
JOHN: Yeah, tell a joke.

20:30.720 --> 20:33.040
What I am trying to say is that...

20:34.800 --> 20:39.360
(STUTTERS) My brother
and the love of a good woman

20:40.680 --> 20:42.840
pulled me through that time.

20:44.440 --> 20:48.520
Now Tommy also
has the love of a good woman.

20:50.080 --> 20:51.920
Her name's Grace.

20:53.480 --> 20:55.720
Like the grace of the good Lord.

20:58.680 --> 20:59.680
And even though

21:01.360 --> 21:05.680
the circumstances of their union
was tragic...

21:05.760 --> 21:08.040
All right. Let's, uh... Arthur.

21:08.120 --> 21:10.160
Let's raise a toast, eh?

21:10.240 --> 21:11.960
To, uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

21:12.040 --> 21:15.600
To love, to peace, to marriage.

21:15.680 --> 21:17.400
-And to marriage.
-To marriage.

21:23.240 --> 21:27.760
JOHN: Well done, Arthur,
beautiful speech. Really nice.

21:29.600 --> 21:30.880
Really, really nice.

21:37.840 --> 21:40.000
JOHN: Where is he fucking going?

21:44.640 --> 21:47.080
-I think I messed it up.
-No, not a bit.

21:47.480 --> 21:49.880
-Hmm.
-You spoke with such truth.

21:50.920 --> 21:52.400
And God heard you.

21:52.480 --> 21:54.120
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

21:55.320 --> 21:58.080
TOMMY: Can I have a word
with my brother, please, Linda?

21:58.640 --> 22:01.600
-What he was going to say was beautiful.
-Mmm-hmm.

22:02.320 --> 22:03.720
Alone, please.

22:09.560 --> 22:10.840
All right. Come here.

22:12.080 --> 22:13.120
Come here.

22:15.000 --> 22:16.480
(TOMMY SIGHS)

22:17.800 --> 22:19.800
We talked about this, Arthur.

22:19.880 --> 22:21.680
That's why we wrote it all down.

22:22.800 --> 22:26.680
Most of Grace's side don't even know
her husband killed himself.

22:26.760 --> 22:27.960
They think it was an accident.

22:28.960 --> 22:30.240
-Oh, I know.
-You know.

22:31.440 --> 22:32.640
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

22:32.720 --> 22:34.280
What do you think I am? Hmm?

22:35.880 --> 22:37.920
What do you think I am, Tommy, eh?

22:38.480 --> 22:41.440
-You think I'm a fucking idiot!
-All right, boys.

22:41.520 --> 22:44.680
-Come on, have a good night.
-You think I would say it...

22:44.760 --> 22:47.360
-Come on, then. That's it.
-You keep walking, you nosy bastards.

22:47.440 --> 22:50.080
-Arthur.
-You stay away from me.

22:50.160 --> 22:52.800
-Fuck in hell.
-You stay away from me. I've had enough.

22:55.440 --> 22:56.440
Ah!

22:56.800 --> 22:57.840
Shit.

22:58.360 --> 23:00.240
-(GROANING)
-Yeah. Yeah.

23:04.920 --> 23:06.680
(ARTHUR GROANS)

23:09.280 --> 23:10.720
Ah, shit.

23:12.560 --> 23:15.040
Three shots I've had. That's it.

23:15.120 --> 23:16.760
-TOMMY: I know.
-I drew the line.

23:16.840 --> 23:17.880
I know.

23:17.960 --> 23:20.440
I know you've turned a corner, Arthur.

23:20.520 --> 23:21.840
-Yeah.
-I know.

23:21.920 --> 23:22.960
-Yeah.
-Mmm-hmm.

23:23.040 --> 23:24.320
-I'm your best man.
-I know.

23:25.360 --> 23:26.840
I wasn't going to tell no one.

23:26.920 --> 23:28.120
(WHISPERS) It's all right.

23:28.920 --> 23:30.880
It's done. Get up. Get up.

23:31.600 --> 23:32.760
-Get up.
-(GROANS)

23:33.960 --> 23:35.080
Right.

23:36.240 --> 23:39.120
The Russians have made contact.

23:39.640 --> 23:41.840
We have to get used to
how these bastards operate.

23:42.360 --> 23:43.440
For them,

23:43.520 --> 23:45.920
family is a weakness,
and they go after them.

23:46.000 --> 23:49.440
For me, family is my strength.
And there's business to be done.

23:49.520 --> 23:51.320
And I need you.

23:51.400 --> 23:53.640
Now, fuck speeches, fuck weddings.

23:54.160 --> 23:56.480
You're my best man every fucking day.

23:57.960 --> 23:59.600
-OK.
-Yeah.

24:00.160 --> 24:02.720
Now go and get John, get him sobered up.

24:02.800 --> 24:04.200
Find Johnny Dogs.

24:04.280 --> 24:06.680
It's the Russians
through the smoke tonight.

24:08.640 --> 24:10.080
All right.

24:10.160 --> 24:11.240
Good.

24:14.440 --> 24:15.440
And, Arthur?

24:18.040 --> 24:21.440
In future, it's not always right
to listen to Linda.

24:22.200 --> 24:23.360
-Yeah? Yeah.
-Yeah.

24:28.920 --> 24:30.880
-(MUSIC PLAYING)
-(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

24:32.120 --> 24:34.000
It's full of gypsies and blacks.

24:34.080 --> 24:37.200
Grace says he exports automobiles
to the colonies.

24:40.920 --> 24:42.520
TOMMY: Pol, now.

24:47.480 --> 24:48.800
So what does he say?

24:49.840 --> 24:52.360
He won't meet you
unless you give us the name.

24:52.440 --> 24:54.040
What name?

24:54.120 --> 24:57.280
We were told to ask for a code name
when contact was made.

25:00.080 --> 25:03.200
Constantine. The code is Constantine.

25:11.800 --> 25:14.000
Tommy said no racing, no gambling.

25:14.080 --> 25:15.720
Yeah, he's changed his mind.

25:15.800 --> 25:18.000
-Right. Don't worry, Finn, OK?
-Right. (CHUCKLES)

25:18.080 --> 25:20.080
Cavalry boys ride like a sack of stones,
all right?

25:20.160 --> 25:23.680
John. John, there's an awful lot
of King's shillings around here today.

25:23.760 --> 25:26.120
Now, out of loyalty to the regiment,

25:26.200 --> 25:28.280
they'll all be putting their money
on this bad boy

25:28.360 --> 25:31.360
that I filled up
with morphine and water.

25:31.440 --> 25:34.360
Here. Tommy's all right if I, uh,
do the book, is he?

25:34.440 --> 25:38.840
He said betting's OK, but all proceeds
go to the Shelby Foundation charity.

25:38.920 --> 25:41.000
Oh, is this charity of his
for real, then?

25:41.080 --> 25:43.960
He says he wants to be seen
giving back to the poor of Birmingham.

25:44.040 --> 25:45.640
So that'll be me, John.

25:45.720 --> 25:48.160
Myself.
If I can't earn a shilling here tonight.

25:48.240 --> 25:49.280
Huh?

25:49.360 --> 25:51.640
They'll make him
the fucking Lord Mayor next.

25:51.720 --> 25:53.520
Mmm, that's the idea, Charlie-Boy.

25:54.080 --> 25:55.400
Fucking hell.

25:55.480 --> 25:59.040
Right, all you lot
make as much noise and fuss as you can.

25:59.120 --> 26:00.520
Especially fucking you.

26:00.600 --> 26:02.200
So we're a fucking distraction, John,
is it?

26:02.280 --> 26:03.320
-(BOTH LAUGHING)
-Huh?

26:03.400 --> 26:06.520
Tommy is doing business on a night
he should be just fucking.

26:06.600 --> 26:08.320
(LAUGHING)

26:08.400 --> 26:10.600
Right, place your bets with me.

26:10.680 --> 26:12.720
Your favourites. Your favourites.

26:12.800 --> 26:13.840
Come on, boys.

26:13.920 --> 26:17.400
'Cause I hope my boy Finn
doesn't fall off that fucking horse.

26:17.880 --> 26:18.960
Come on.

26:19.040 --> 26:20.040
For charity.

26:20.440 --> 26:21.640
CURLY: Shut up.

26:26.560 --> 26:27.840
ARTHUR: Oh, you found it.

26:28.480 --> 26:29.680
We nearly gave up.

26:38.600 --> 26:41.080
Did he tell you
what my business with him is?

26:46.840 --> 26:48.520
The same shit the Turks used to smoke.

26:50.160 --> 26:51.200
I wonder,

26:51.720 --> 26:54.160
why does he trust his aunt
more than his brothers?

26:55.240 --> 26:56.760
(CHUCKLES)

26:59.520 --> 27:01.240
TOMMY: Go and watch the race, boys.

27:03.320 --> 27:04.800
The Turk's clean.

27:07.360 --> 27:09.120
I am Russian.

27:09.840 --> 27:11.560
Same fucking thing.

27:32.440 --> 27:34.680
So you make contact on my wedding day.

27:34.760 --> 27:36.720
You now have very powerful enemies.

27:37.720 --> 27:40.520
At the Soviet Embassy
and within your own government.

27:40.600 --> 27:42.040
You are being watched,

27:42.120 --> 27:46.080
at your house, your office, your clubs,

27:46.800 --> 27:48.200
your bars.

27:48.280 --> 27:51.080
You best be quick or I'll be missed.
Where's the money?

27:51.160 --> 27:53.520
The Duke's niece
is bringing it from London.

27:55.520 --> 27:57.320
I was told money on contact.

27:58.000 --> 28:00.360
Ten thousand in US dollars.

28:01.560 --> 28:04.560
My employer only trusts
members of his family with cash.

28:05.480 --> 28:07.520
She will be at Snow Hill Station
at 10:00.

28:07.680 --> 28:09.000
(CHUCKLES)

28:10.040 --> 28:15.400
A woman alone in Birmingham
with $10,000 in cash.

28:16.160 --> 28:18.240
-And she also has a revolver.
-Oh, I see.

28:18.320 --> 28:19.920
I thought you trusted women.

28:20.000 --> 28:21.920
I don't trust Birmingham.

28:22.000 --> 28:23.720
I'll have her picked up.

28:23.800 --> 28:26.160
-By who?
-By the police, pal.

28:26.960 --> 28:28.240
This is our city.

28:37.360 --> 28:39.120
(ALL CHEERING)

28:49.520 --> 28:51.520
ARTHUR: Fucking beautiful horse, Tom.

28:53.280 --> 28:54.320
Beautiful.

28:55.360 --> 28:57.120
-He's a natural, that boy.
-Yeah.

28:57.200 --> 28:59.400
Good posture. Rides like Dad.

28:59.480 --> 29:00.520
TOMMY: All right, listen to me.

29:00.600 --> 29:04.520
Tell Johnny Dogs and his boys
to light a fire in the woods,

29:04.600 --> 29:06.360
a big one, to take meat.

29:07.440 --> 29:09.360
And send Finn to watch the gates.

29:09.440 --> 29:11.120
Moss is bringing someone.

29:17.440 --> 29:18.600
CHARLOTTE: You don't?

29:21.160 --> 29:23.840
I just needed to bring you somewhere
nobody could see.

29:23.920 --> 29:26.520
But your friend gave this to me.
He said you all did it.

29:27.400 --> 29:28.600
Not me.

29:28.680 --> 29:30.800
But it's all right. Go on.

29:36.840 --> 29:37.960
(MICHAEL CHUCKLES)

29:38.040 --> 29:39.480
I see you don't, either.

29:40.520 --> 29:43.040
-Don't be silly, everyone does.
-So go on, then.

29:43.200 --> 29:46.040
-(SIGHS) Cut the snow.
-We call it Tokyo.

29:46.120 --> 29:48.080
We call it whatever
the customer calls it.

29:48.800 --> 29:52.200
In London,
we were told you are all gangsters.

29:52.760 --> 29:55.800
So that's why you got on the train
to dirty, old Birmingham.

29:57.120 --> 29:58.800
For a dirty, old night.

30:02.200 --> 30:03.760
You don't look like the others.

30:03.840 --> 30:05.160
That's the idea.

30:06.360 --> 30:08.800
I put it all together,
but I don't partake.

30:10.240 --> 30:13.080
You see, I've got a bright future,
you see.

30:15.720 --> 30:16.960
Mapped out.

30:22.160 --> 30:24.400
But you want me to be like them,
don't you?

30:30.960 --> 30:33.600
There's a cavalry officer
stationed in Ceylon.

30:33.680 --> 30:36.800
And when his tour of duty ends in March,
we'll be engaged.

30:38.600 --> 30:42.080
So I have a bright future, too.

30:43.080 --> 30:44.480
Mapped out.

30:45.400 --> 30:47.440
But you want to try things first.

30:57.560 --> 30:58.840
(SNORTS)

31:00.560 --> 31:02.000
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

31:09.440 --> 31:10.880
No. Keep it.

31:12.320 --> 31:13.720
As if I were a whore.

31:18.320 --> 31:20.880
Well, if that's the game
you want to play.

31:35.840 --> 31:38.000
(PEOPLE LAUGHING
AND TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

31:42.800 --> 31:43.920
Polly.

31:44.720 --> 31:45.800
Hello, Grace.

31:47.800 --> 31:50.360
You look absolutely beautiful.

31:52.720 --> 31:54.320
Welcome to the family.

31:56.960 --> 31:58.760
Oh, I see. Tommy's orders.

31:59.760 --> 32:01.000
No upsets tonight.

32:01.080 --> 32:04.440
Your hair, everything, beautiful.

32:06.360 --> 32:07.600
Do you know where he is?

32:08.360 --> 32:11.120
Yes. Yes, I do.

32:13.080 --> 32:16.760
You know, Tommy really wants to keep
certain things a secret from me.

32:18.320 --> 32:20.240
It's very hard when you're man and wife.

32:20.720 --> 32:23.440
We were late coming down
because we were having sex.

32:23.920 --> 32:25.760
So afterwards, he told me everything.

32:28.720 --> 32:32.880
Royalist Russians buying weapons
to fight the Bolsheviks in Georgia.

32:35.000 --> 32:36.760
A lost cause, Tommy says.

32:38.080 --> 32:40.520
And Churchill, he's the go-between.

32:40.600 --> 32:44.280
But it's against government policy
so everything must be kept a secret.

32:50.880 --> 32:52.000
You know it's begun?

32:55.280 --> 32:57.400
They started the business tonight?

33:02.720 --> 33:03.920
No. (SIGHS)

33:05.840 --> 33:07.120
I didn't.

33:09.000 --> 33:10.840
But you just told me.

33:10.920 --> 33:12.360
So, thank you.

33:15.760 --> 33:18.240
Let's not forget
I used to do this for a living.

33:20.560 --> 33:22.360
Oh, I haven't forgotten, sweetheart.

33:24.080 --> 33:26.200
It's only Thomas that's forgotten
what you are.

33:26.280 --> 33:28.320
MAN: <i>Ladies and Gentlemen.</i>

33:29.080 --> 33:32.800
<i>The bride and the groom
will now dance alone.</i>

33:32.880 --> 33:34.600
(ALL CHEERING)

33:39.160 --> 33:41.000
(MUSIC PLAYING)

33:46.640 --> 33:49.440
Polly just told me
there is business being done.

33:53.040 --> 33:54.320
I didn't ask them to come.

33:56.560 --> 33:59.200
Tommy, please don't let
anything happen tonight.

34:03.440 --> 34:08.200
Just get this business done
and get away from things like this.

34:10.600 --> 34:12.080
I'll run the foundation,

34:13.400 --> 34:16.000
you run the tracks and sell cars.

34:20.480 --> 34:21.680
Promise me.

34:22.760 --> 34:23.800
Hmm?

34:24.720 --> 34:26.240
A wedding vow.

34:27.880 --> 34:29.160
I promise.

34:30.320 --> 34:31.920
No guns in the house

34:32.920 --> 34:35.160
-and Charles will never see one.
-(CHUCKLES)

34:36.800 --> 34:38.480
I love you, Thomas Shelby.

34:40.840 --> 34:42.120
You keep us safe.

34:43.040 --> 34:44.360
I love you.

34:45.440 --> 34:48.960
And I promise I will make us safe.

34:53.680 --> 34:56.600
MAN: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,
you may now join.</i>

35:11.760 --> 35:13.000
Gate house, come on.

35:25.480 --> 35:26.560
(ENGINE STOPS)

35:26.640 --> 35:31.360
Tommy, Arthur, Collins.

35:31.920 --> 35:36.120
May I introduce you to the
Grand Duchess Tatiana Petrovna,

35:37.640 --> 35:39.560
from Tbilisi, Georgia.

35:40.840 --> 35:45.320
Grand Duchess, may I introduce you
to the Shelby brothers.

35:45.880 --> 35:47.480
Small Heath, Birmingham.

35:50.440 --> 35:53.200
And, uh, good luck with this one, Tom.

35:58.320 --> 35:59.720
Give me the money.

36:01.280 --> 36:03.480
I was told to give it to Mr Kaledin.

36:04.120 --> 36:07.160
Whoever it is up there,
he gave the wrong name.

36:08.480 --> 36:11.640
We asked him the name
and he gave the wrong one.

36:12.200 --> 36:14.360
-What name did he give?
-No.

36:16.440 --> 36:18.280
I don't trust any of you.

36:19.720 --> 36:21.200
Now you give me the money.

36:22.840 --> 36:26.720
I know Mr Kaledin by sight from Tbilisi.
Is his hair dark?

36:26.800 --> 36:28.880
The instructions I was given

36:28.960 --> 36:30.720
was anyone using the wrong code name

36:30.800 --> 36:33.360
was an infiltrator
for the Soviet Embassy.

36:34.720 --> 36:35.760
Just let me go to the house.

36:35.840 --> 36:39.240
I do not want this shit
anywhere near my fucking house.

36:44.320 --> 36:46.800
All I know is "no variations."

36:47.680 --> 36:49.800
That's from Churchill himself.

36:49.880 --> 36:53.000
Whoever it is up at the house,
he gave the wrong fucking name.

36:56.280 --> 37:00.400
And you do this to me
on my fucking wedding day.

37:00.600 --> 37:01.640
(CLICKS TONGUE)

37:03.400 --> 37:05.440
The money is in the car, Mr Shelby.

37:06.800 --> 37:08.240
Fetch it out and count it.

37:09.800 --> 37:12.120
Good. Finn.

37:17.880 --> 37:19.120
(COUGHS)

37:32.600 --> 37:34.920
Yeah. We're good.

37:36.280 --> 37:38.480
You can go. Moss... (CLEARS THROAT)

37:38.920 --> 37:39.960
Can you do it?

37:42.720 --> 37:44.080
Can you kill?

37:48.680 --> 37:53.680
Moss, you take the "Duchess"
back to Birmingham.

37:55.280 --> 37:56.360
MOSS: Righto Tom.

37:58.040 --> 37:59.160
Come on, love.

38:02.280 --> 38:03.320
That's right.

38:07.120 --> 38:08.800
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

38:10.840 --> 38:12.520
You have got to tell me the reason,

38:12.600 --> 38:15.000
otherwise I'll never be able
to trust you.

38:15.920 --> 38:17.440
The truth is,

38:19.760 --> 38:22.640
that I slept with the wife of
one of the colonels who sat for me.

38:23.800 --> 38:25.560
But that was 12 years ago.

38:27.680 --> 38:30.280
And the aristocracy
don't believe in forgiveness.

38:34.240 --> 38:35.880
Neither do the Shelbys.

38:44.360 --> 38:45.520
(ENGINE STOPS)

38:53.480 --> 38:54.800
So, we kill him?

38:55.520 --> 38:56.600
He's a red.

38:58.920 --> 39:02.320
We're being paid by the whites.
It's part of the contract.

39:02.400 --> 39:03.800
Contract.

39:07.400 --> 39:09.120
We should never have got into this, Tom.

39:10.440 --> 39:11.880
There was no choice.

39:13.840 --> 39:17.840
"A factory break-in,"
that's what you said.

39:17.920 --> 39:20.080
Yeah. And that's what it is.

39:22.200 --> 39:24.640
There's just some shit
that goes with it.

39:32.360 --> 39:33.880
And who shovels it? Hmm?

39:36.720 --> 39:40.600
Who fucking shovels it? Eh?

39:42.160 --> 39:43.560
I fucking know.

39:44.480 --> 39:46.240
-Arthur?
-I fucking know.

39:46.320 --> 39:47.520
Arthur.

39:48.560 --> 39:51.480
There's 10 times where
that's coming from, 10 times.

39:51.560 --> 39:53.480
For lifting vehicles
off a fucking shop floor.

39:53.560 --> 39:56.480
Vehicles, Tommy. Fucking vehicles.

39:56.560 --> 39:58.440
-Nothing about tanks.

39:59.000 --> 40:02.840
Arthur, you listen to me.
You listen to me, all right?

40:02.920 --> 40:05.280
There are powerful people
in this country

40:05.360 --> 40:06.800
who want to help these mad bastards,

40:06.880 --> 40:10.440
including the King, Churchill
and half the fucking Tory Party.

40:10.520 --> 40:14.240
And if we refuse, Arthur,
if we fucking refuse,

40:14.800 --> 40:18.120
they will see to it
that we hang for one of our many sins.

40:18.200 --> 40:20.840
Now, we've never earned money
like this. Never.

40:21.720 --> 40:25.280
We'll use it to buy
the wharf at Boston docks.

40:25.360 --> 40:27.040
That's why I've asked for dollars.

40:28.600 --> 40:31.720
And when it's done,
it's business as usual.

40:39.000 --> 40:41.960
Come on, brother. It's my wedding night.

40:48.080 --> 40:48.640
(CHATTERING)

40:48.640 --> 40:49.440
(CHATTERING)

40:49.520 --> 40:51.840
-Where's John?
-Looking for Esme.

40:51.920 --> 40:53.000
Right.

40:53.640 --> 40:55.320
Ruben Oliver, portrait artist.

40:55.920 --> 40:59.160
I really enjoyed the depiction of you
in the dining room.

40:59.240 --> 41:00.440
(SPEAKING ROMANY)

41:10.080 --> 41:11.960
Nice to meet you, Mr Oliver.

41:18.120 --> 41:19.480
Johnny, ragtime.

41:19.560 --> 41:21.200
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

42:12.080 --> 42:13.360
(SIGHS)

42:20.560 --> 42:22.000
So, where were we?

42:22.840 --> 42:25.920
-Crimea.
-Oh, I mean before I bored you with war.

42:26.000 --> 42:27.040
(CHUCKLES)

42:27.120 --> 42:28.920
-Politics.
-Ah, yes.

42:31.920 --> 42:34.880
You're the only one in your family
who is a communist?

42:35.640 --> 42:38.280
Some of them are,
they just don't know it.

42:38.360 --> 42:41.400
(CHUCKLES) And you are
a very close family, yes?

42:41.520 --> 42:44.200
Mmm, always within punching distance.

42:45.320 --> 42:46.600
What does that mean?

42:47.760 --> 42:49.840
It means, "Yeah, we're a close family."

42:54.880 --> 42:56.680
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

43:03.640 --> 43:04.680
Arthur?

43:06.760 --> 43:08.920
I do apologise for the interruption.

43:10.960 --> 43:13.600
There is a woman here
to see you, Mr Kaledin.

43:14.520 --> 43:16.080
She just arrived.

43:30.520 --> 43:32.400
(LAUGHTER AND INDISTINCT TALKING)

43:38.760 --> 43:41.320
So, Tatiana made it from London safe?

43:41.400 --> 43:43.280
-Yes.
-Where is she?

43:43.360 --> 43:44.840
Out by the stables.

43:55.880 --> 43:57.520
Can I use the lavatory?

44:04.560 --> 44:10.040
You can piss outside by the stables.

44:24.080 --> 44:25.240
No!

44:25.880 --> 44:27.960
(SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

44:29.840 --> 44:31.480
(GROANING)

44:45.920 --> 44:47.840
(MEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

44:49.440 --> 44:51.000
Very sensible idea, Mr Shelby.

44:52.000 --> 44:54.320
Clear the air away from the ladies.

44:54.720 --> 44:56.320
(GRUNTING)

44:56.960 --> 44:58.720
We are rather like generals here,
aren't we?

44:59.920 --> 45:01.920
Watching our men do battle.

45:02.000 --> 45:04.920
We are a bit too close to the fighting
to be generals, surely.

45:05.040 --> 45:06.520
(SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

45:08.160 --> 45:09.760
(PANTING)

45:16.480 --> 45:18.240
(SCREAMING)

45:28.280 --> 45:30.000
(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

45:32.040 --> 45:36.120
You know, Mr Shelby, some of us only
agreed to come today to bless this union

45:36.200 --> 45:38.800
because of your exemplary war record.

45:38.880 --> 45:41.080
But as Grace's uncle

45:41.160 --> 45:44.200
and a kind of father to her
for many years,

45:45.920 --> 45:48.240
I'm still deeply uneasy

45:49.320 --> 45:53.040
about the many stories of corruption
and violence.

45:54.120 --> 45:55.880
(BOTH STRUGGLING)

45:57.240 --> 45:58.800
(SCREAMING)

46:00.640 --> 46:03.160
Drink the fucking wine and smile.

46:04.480 --> 46:05.880
That's what I'm doing.

46:11.240 --> 46:13.280
ARTHUR: Oh, you got me good.

46:18.200 --> 46:20.240
Oh, you fucking bastard.

46:21.120 --> 46:23.000
(ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

46:23.560 --> 46:24.720
No foul!

46:26.840 --> 46:27.880
No foul!

46:31.120 --> 46:32.880
(PANTING)

46:53.200 --> 46:54.640
KALEDIN: Don't shoot.

46:54.720 --> 46:55.840
No!

46:55.920 --> 46:57.200
Oh, for the love of God, don't shoot.

46:57.280 --> 46:59.000
No! No!

46:59.080 --> 47:00.320
-No!
-For the love of God...

47:00.400 --> 47:02.360
-No! No! No!
-For the love of God...

47:03.000 --> 47:04.200
-No!
-For the love of God.

47:04.960 --> 47:06.000
(GUNSHOT)

47:06.080 --> 47:08.080
-What was that?
-(BOTH PANTING)

47:08.160 --> 47:10.160
It's probably just a car back-firing.

47:10.520 --> 47:12.160
(PANTING)

47:49.600 --> 47:51.720
It wasn't the day I was expecting.

47:53.160 --> 47:54.360
Nor me.

47:58.320 --> 47:59.520
It's over now.

48:01.600 --> 48:03.320
Tomorrow it'll be just us.

48:08.960 --> 48:10.320
(SIGHS)

48:11.520 --> 48:12.640
Come here.

48:25.560 --> 48:27.360
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

48:27.440 --> 48:30.080
CURLY: Go on.
You've had a great night.

49:00.760 --> 49:02.160
The water froze in my car.

49:03.800 --> 49:05.400
Uh, they said I could stay.

49:06.400 --> 49:09.600
I know, this is preposterous.

49:10.360 --> 49:12.520
Plenty of other rooms to stay in.

49:17.160 --> 49:19.400
-Goodnight, Mr Oliver.
-You have my card.

49:20.440 --> 49:22.000
Anytime you're in London,

49:22.760 --> 49:24.760
we could have tea.

49:59.760 --> 50:01.560
ARTHUR: I went looking for you.

50:04.080 --> 50:05.600
I thought you'd be in here.

50:07.000 --> 50:08.120
I knew it.

50:09.400 --> 50:11.480
I wanted to end with a bit of peace.

50:12.120 --> 50:13.280
(WHISPERS) Yeah.

50:14.880 --> 50:16.040
Look what I found.

50:18.080 --> 50:20.720
It's beautiful. Thanks.

50:32.000 --> 50:35.080
Arthur, you mustn't worry about
what happened with the speech.

50:40.400 --> 50:43.680
What was in your heart was beautiful.

50:49.200 --> 50:51.800
God hears all the speeches
that don't get said.

50:55.680 --> 50:59.120
And isn't it nice to still be yourself
at this time of night?

51:04.360 --> 51:07.360
Close your eyes, Arthur,
and spend a minute thinking about that.

51:10.920 --> 51:12.600
(MUSIC PLAYING)

51:32.040 --> 51:33.920
(BABY CRYING)

51:34.000 --> 51:35.520
TOMMY: It's all right.

51:35.600 --> 51:36.800
It's all right.

51:49.760 --> 51:50.800
(SHUSHING)

53:05.440 --> 53:06.560
(INAUDIBLE)

53:52.560 --> 53:54.440
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

54:35.760 --> 54:39.920
More money than all those
fucking toffs put together, eh?

54:41.280 --> 54:44.320
And you're willing to gamble it all
on one robbery.

54:46.080 --> 54:47.720
I'm a gambling man, Pol.

54:48.800 --> 54:50.800
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

55:05.920 --> 55:11.480
<i># Take a little walk to the edge of town
and go across the track #</i>

55:11.504 --> 55:16.504
http://hiqve.com/
